Even the president elect...
This goes for things as taboo as racism, sexism, gender equality, religion, etc
I won't physically hurt you, and won't stand by as you get attacked, for saying what you believe in

So I say, speak your mind, as I will mine

And we'll come down to a conclusion through critical reasoning

Even if it offends you, as soon as that power of speech is taken from you

Your "freedom" becomes tailored

Speech is speech and won't physically harm you

Don't let an upper power determine what is and isn't allowed to be spoken

Acknowledge those born and brought up in worse conditions

God blessed my good fortune, to the point my misfortunes are blessings of their own
Poverty isn't over, violence isn't over, pain, suffering, loneliness, isn't over in this world
